[1]
Date: Fri 20 Jul 2018
Source: WHO Weekly Bulletin on Outbreaks and Other Emergencies [edited]
http://apps.who.int/iris/bitstream/handle/10665/273214/OEW29-1420072018.pdf


An outbreak of Rift Valley fever (RVF) was confirmed on [Thu 28 Jun 2018]. As of [Tue 17 Jul 2018], 8 cases (6 confirmed and 2 suspected), including 3 deaths (CFR: 42 percent), were reported from west and central Uganda. The 6 confirmed cases were reported from 5 different districts: one from Kasese, 2 from Isingiro, one from Ibanda, one from Mbarara, and one from Sembabule district. One suspected case, identified on arrival at Mbarara Regional Referral Hospital, ran away from the isolation ward before any further assessment was done. The 2nd is waiting for results and is in the isolation ward. All cases were confirmed by PCR at UVRI (Uganda Virology Research Institute).

